    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Spiritual places in the Inca religion. Included are Pre-Columbian Inca tombs or temples, usually a truncated pyramid of stone, and often of immense size. Huacas could also be caves, springs, special rocks, and man-made shrines.</Note_Text>
